I've added non-goals, user journeys, and alternatives we discussed with the
WebAuthn WG to the explainer
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/w3c/webauthn/wiki/Explainer:-WebAuthn-Signal-API-explainer"&gt;https://github.com/w3c/webauthn/wiki/Explainer:-WebAuthn-Signal-API-explainer&lt;/a&gt;&gt;
.

In terms of the names of the methods, they were vetted by the WebAuthn WG
and we do not expect them to change. We've already had our own fair share
of bikeshedding (:


